# Features

## Missing/Incomplete Features

☐ Article bookmarking / read-later queue — Star rating exists (1-5) but there's no dedicated "save for later" or bookmarks list. A simple boolean isBookmarked with a Bookmarks sidebar section would be high-value.
☐ Export / share — No way to share article links externally (system share sheet, copy link, etc.). macOS has a native Share button that integrates with Safari, Notes, etc.
☐ Keyboard navigation — No apparent keyboard shortcuts for navigating between articles (J/K like classic RSS readers), marking read (M), starring (S), or opening detail (Enter/Space). These are expected by power users.
☐ Fetch on launch / auto-refresh — There's no background periodic refresh. The app only fetches when the user manually hits Refresh or adds a source. A configurable auto-refresh interval (e.g., every 15/30/60 min) would keep the feed current.
☐ Unread count badges — SidebarView shows unread count for "All Articles" but it's unclear if per-source unread counts appear. Even a small badge per source helps navigation.
☐ Mark all read — No bulk "mark all as read" action. Users accumulate hundreds of articles fast.
☐ OPML import/export — RSS managers conventionally support OPML for migrating feed lists. Without it, switching to/from Reeder, NetNewsWire, etc. is painful.
☐ Article text size / font controls — ArticleWebContentView hardcodes 17px Georgia. A font-size slider in Settings (or toolbar) would help readability.
☐ AI batch processing — Ollama rewrites happen one article at a time, triggered manually. A "rewrite all visible headlines" batch option would make the AI feature much more useful.
☐ Image gallery / full-screen image — No way to zoom/expand thumbnail images in article detail.

## Usability

☐ Article detail is a sheet, not a split panel — On a large macOS display, a NavigationSplitView with a third detail column would be far more natural than a full-screen modal sheet. The current sheet covers the entire grid and kills browsing momentum.
☐ Read articles don't persist scroll position — When the user returns from article detail, the grid likely resets. Scroll position should be preserved across detail open/close.
☐ No "next article" / "previous article" navigation in detail — Users have to close the sheet and reopen the next card. An arrow button (or swipe gesture) to step through articles sequentially is a basic reader feature.
☐ Tag filter is all-or-nothing — Tags appear to be AND or OR but it's not communicated. Clarifying the filter logic (or letting users toggle it) prevents confusion.
☐ Source error is in context menu only — The warning icon on a source with lastError only reveals the error via right-click. Hovering to show a tooltip with the error text would be much more discoverable.
☐ No confirmation on "Hide article" — The hide button appears on hover with no undo. A brief "Undo" toast/notification would prevent accidental hides.
☐ Search scope is unclear — Does search cover title only? Author? Summary? Content? There's no indication, and users will be confused by non-obvious results.
☐ Settings are in a separate window — The Ollama + weather settings are in a standard Settings scene, but some of these (especially Ollama model selection ad test connection) feel like they belong in the Source Manager or a quick-access popover.
☐ No loading indicator at the per-source level — During refresh, you can't tell which sources are currently fetching vs. done. A subtle spinner next to each source in the sidebar would help.

## Performance

☐ ReadabilityService uses WKWebView on every detail open — Even for cached articles, loadContent() in ArticleDetailViewModel still invokes the Readability pipeline if readableContent is nil. Cached content should short-circuit immediately without touching WKWebView at all.
☐ Image loading has no explicit cache policy — AsyncImage uses the default URL cache. For a news app where the same thumbnail may appear on the grid card and in the detail view, using URLCache with a defined size limit or a proper image cache (e.g., NSCache) would reduce redundant network hits.
☐ Tag filtering runs a full DB query on every keypress in search — applySearch in ArticlesViewModel triggers initialLoad(). A debounce (e.g., 300ms) on searchText changes would reduce needless DB hits.
☐ Parallel feed refresh with no concurrency cap — FeedRefreshService uses TaskGroup to fetch all enabled sources simultaneously. With 30+ sources enabled, this spawns 30+ concurrent network requests. A bounded semaphore or withTaskGroup with a max parallelism of ~5-8 would be more resource-friendly.
☐ rewriteWithAI is called on a per-article basis with no queue — If a user triggers multiple AI rewrites in rapid succession, they go to Ollama serially and each blocks on a response. An AsyncStream-based queue with cancellation support would be cleaner.
☐ Pagination prefetch threshold of 10 items — With 40-item pages, triggering prefetch at 10 items remaining is probably fine, but the next page load is synchronous-feeling. Pre-fetching at 15-20 items with smooth skeleton insertion would eliminate visible load pauses.

## UI Usability

☐ Article grid uses a single adaptive column (280–400pt) — On a large monitor (27–32"), this results in 3-4 very wide cards. A true multi-column newspaper layout (e.g., 2–3 fixed columns like a broadsheet) would be far more appropriate for the "newspaper" aesthetic.
☐ Tag chips have no maximum width enforcement — Long tag names can stretch the filter bar awkwardly. Truncating chip labels at ~12 chars with a tooltip would tighten the bar.
☐ Hover-only hide button is discoverable only by accident — Consider making it always-visible as a faint X, or accessible via right-click context menu.
☐ NewspaperHeaderView masthead disappears on scroll — The header likely scrolls away with the grid. Keeping the masthead pinned (sticky header) would reinforce the newspaper identity and keep weather + date visible.
☐ Star ratings on the card are too small for confident clicking — 5 star symbols at 14pt article card density are easy to mis-tap. Moving ratings to the detail view (where there's space) or making stars larger on hover would help.
☐ No dark mode thumbnail handling — Dark mode likely inverts some article thumbnails oddly depending on image content. A subtle darkening overlay on thumbnails in dark mode would look more consistent.
☐ Skeleton loading uses fixed 4 cards — If the user has 1-2 articles visible before paginating, 4 skeleton cards will overshoot the visible area. Calculating the visible row count and matching the skeleton count would look cleaner.
☐ Source color assignment via hash is invisible to the user — Users can't customize source colors. A color picker per source in Source Manager would let them create their own visual taxonomy.
☐ "THE DAILY FEED" masthead is always the same regardless of filter — When the user is viewing a single source or a tag filter, the header could reflect that context (e.g., "THE DAILY FEED / Technology" or the source's name).
☐ Empty state messaging could be more specific — When articles are empty due to a search that returns nothing vs. all sources being disabled vs. no articles fetched yet, the same empty state likely appears. Contextual empty states improve clarity.

